usage: %s [c FILE] | [d CONTENT CRC_FILE]
usage: objcopy --add-section .gnu_debuglink=<(dbgltool d ../whatever <(dbgltool c ../whatever ))
The c mode calculates and prints the crc of the file.
The d mode constructs and prints data according to the .gnu_debuglink description
dbgltool (debuglink tool) is a small tool for generating .gnu_debuglink data without restrictions (buyer beware).
Specifically, without the basename restriction.
The set value can be checked with a hex viewer such as xxd and objdump, or readelf, e.g.: `readelf -x .gnu_debuglink filename`.
you can edit test binaries with `objcopy --add-gnu-debuglink` and other appropriate objcopy flags.
See also https://sourceware.org/gdb/onlinedocs/gdb/Separate-Debug-Files.html
